race.comment: TROIKA (7) improved again at Doomben and then was beaten a whisker at the Sunshine Coast at this level. That's good form for this contest. Loves the trip, and he can make his first visit to Ipswich a winning one. THELWELL (6) was slightly planer last time, but rates well on his Gold Coast effort the one before. Maps well and keeps the handy 2kg claim. Has been kept on the fresh side and can fight out the finish. MAXIMUM OUTPUT (1) found an Open at Eagle Farm too much of a stretch seeking the hat-trick off wins here and at the Gold Coast. Better suited and he can get back on track. DON'T STOP (2) is third-up and was winning range last time in a 90 at Doomben. Was beaten 2L in Stakes grade here before the spell. The inside gate should advantage and he'd be right in the finish finding his best.
